# <type>[optional scope]: <description>

# [optional body]

# [optional footer(s)]


# tips for commit. for more info - https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
# type: fix, feat, perf, docs, refactor, style, chore, merge, test, build, ci, logs
# description: correct, resolve, adjust, update, add, implement, remove, refactor, optimize
# add ! for breaking change and/or BREAKING CHANGE: at the footer
# scope: should be specific parts of the code you touched like fixi_state or client
# body: start with a verb, imperative present tense. No "." at the end. No capitalizaiton
# think of following the sentence "this commit should/will"
# footer types: Fixes/Closes/Resolves, Relates-to/References/See-also, Co-authored-by, Reviewed-by, Signed-off-by

